The probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn is $r / (r + 9)$, and the probability of drawing a blue ball is $9 / (r + 9)$.

## Step 3: Determine the probability of getting two balls of the same color
To get two balls of the same color, we can either draw two red balls or two blue balls. The probability of drawing two red balls is $(8/15) \times (r / (r + 9))$, and the probability of drawing two blue balls is $(7/15) \times (9 / (r + 9))$. The total probability of getting two balls of the same color is the sum of these two probabilities: $(8/15) \times (r / (r + 9)) + (7/15) \times (9 / (r + 9)) = 151 / 300$.

## Step 4: Set up the equation based on the given probability
$(8r / (15(r + 9))) + (7 \times 9 / (15(r + 9))) = 151 / 300$. Simplifying this gives $(8r + 63) / (15(r + 9)) = 151 / 300$.

